result.execSummary:
The defendant Derek L. Huntington was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Domestic Abuse Repeater], an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: DA Fox appeared on behalf of the State.  Defendant appeared in person, in custody with Attorney Fredrickson.  Court advises defendant of the charge, and enhancers.  Defendant understands.   Defendant plead no contest to the charge.  Court reviewed plea questionnaire, element and constitutional rights waived with defendant.  Find that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Find factual basis.  Felony warning given. Find guilty as charged. Victim makes statement.  State recommended 9 months jail, consecutive to sentences now serving.  Defense recommended 90 days jail consecutive to sentences now serving.   Defendant did not make a statement.  Court ordered:  11 months jail consecutive to sentence now serving.  CC.  Credit for 17 days.
